{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "invoice-payment-service-collection",
    "name": "Invoice & Payment Service",
    "description": "Invoice & Payment Service \u2014 single collection file (no separate environment).\n\nFIRST API KEY:\n1. docker compose up --build\n2. Run \"First API Key - POST /bootstrap\" (no auth) \u2014 saves apiKey automatically\n3. Or fresh DB only: docker compose logs api | grep \"TEST API KEY\"\n\nROTATE (needs apiKey): List API Keys \u2192 Create API Key (rotate).\n\nVariables: baseUrl, pspBaseUrl, apiKey, apiKeyId, customerId, invoiceId, webhookUrl, savedIdemKey",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{apiKey}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "pspBaseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:9090",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "apiKey",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Set automatically by POST /bootstrap, or paste from docker logs on first empty DB."
    },
    {
      "key": "apiKeyId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "ID of current api key (from List API Keys) for revoke on rotate"
    },
    {
      "key": "savedIdemKey",
      "value": "idem-key-fixed-001",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "customerId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "invoiceId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "webhookUrl",
      "value": "https://webhook.site/your-unique-id",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "00 - Setup & Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "SETUP - Edit Collection Variables",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "8080",
              "path": [
                "health"
              ]
            },
            "description": "See request: First API Key - from Docker logs.\n\nPostgres host port 5433; API 8080; mock PSP 9090."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('API up', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "First API Key - POST /bootstrap",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/bootstrap",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8080",
              "path": ["bootstrap"]
            },
            "description": "Gets the first API key (no Bearer token needed).\n\nWorks when no active API keys exist (fresh DB or all keys revoked).\nReturns 409 if an active key already exists — use POST /api-keys to rotate instead.\n\nOn success, test script saves api_key into collection variable apiKey."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('got api_key', () => pm.expect(j.api_key).to.match(/^sk_/));",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('apiKey', j.api_key);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('apiKeyId', j.id);",
                  "  console.log('apiKey saved to collection variables');",
                  "} else if (pm.response.code === 409) {",
                  "  pm.test('already bootstrapped', () => true);",
                  "  console.warn('Active key exists. Set apiKey manually or use Create API Key (rotate).');",
                  "} else {",
                  "  pm.test('bootstrap failed', () => { throw new Error(pm.response.text()); });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "8080",
              "path": [
                "health"
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('status ok', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('ok'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "List API Keys",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api-keys",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8080",
              "path": ["api-keys"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const data = pm.response.json().data || [];",
                  "const active = data.find(k => !k.revoked_at);",
                  "if (active) pm.collectionVariables.set('apiKeyId', active.id);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Create API Key (rotate)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"revoke_key_id\": \"{{apiKeyId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api-keys",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8080",
              "path": ["api-keys"]
            },
            "description": "ROTATION ONLY — requires apiKey already set from Docker logs (bootstrap).\n\nCreates new key. If apiKeyId is set, revokes the old key. Save api_key from response into collection variable apiKey."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('has api_key', () => pm.expect(j.api_key).to.match(/^sk_/));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('apiKey', j.api_key);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('apiKeyId', j.id);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Revoke API Key by ID",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api-keys/{{apiKeyId}}",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8080",
              "path": ["api-keys", "{{apiKeyId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Revokes the key in apiKeyId. Use a different active key in apiKey variable before revoking the one you are testing."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
